race.comment: DASH BY (10) talented mare going nicely through her grades. Won her last two starts in good style but she doesn't get the same map favours her. Will appreciate the claim again and races best with the runs spaced. Go close. THINK WE'RE THERE (5) hard fit for this and capable of better after racing without cover from the awkward gate when sixth over 2000m at Beaumont (Newcastle). Gets map favours today and no surprise to see him return to winning form. MISSION BRAVO (6) outclassed when sent to town for a plodding eleventh over 2200m at Warwick Farm in BM64 grade. Undefeated at this track and winning apprentice hops back aboard. Each way. FIGHTING MAGNUS (9) struggling of late over the shorter trips and assess on his good third four starts back at Newcastle. One for the exotics.
